<TITLE> Man shot and mugged at Moghbazaar </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 30 (bdnews24.com)Muggers shot and robbed a man of Tk 5.50 lakh at Mogbazaar in the capital on Tuesday. Swapan Kapali, account of Dhaka Christian Cooperative Association, was heading for Rupali Bank to deposit Tk 5.50 lakh from the Mogbazar office at around 11:30am, colleague Bibhash said. Four muggers with two motorcycles tried to take the bag containing the money away. As Kapali tried to resist, the miscreants shot him in the left leg and took away the money, Bibhash said. Swapan was admitted to Dhaka Medical College Hospital. Ramna police chief Shibli Noman said they had heard the news. "We are looking into the matter," he said. bd
